[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3]Vanilla makes wooden pallets hard to come by and the cellar pallets aren't player-built at all. This mod opens pallets up as a normal buildable and smooths out the cellar handling that goes with them.[/size]

[size=3][b]Buildable pallet[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Wooden pallet[/b] — added to the wooden build desk and the cellar build desk from the start of the game. Costs 6 flitch and 4 nails.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Removable[/b] — pallets can be deconstructed via the build desk's Remove button, returning half the build cost.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Cellar handling[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Whole cellar pulls its weight[/b] — vanilla dumps crates at the base of the elevator in no particular pattern. Pallets you build anywhere in the cellar storage area now get fed by the elevator and emptied by the porter the same way the originals do.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Loose crates auto-route to pallets[/b] — any crate lying on the floor when you load a save gets slid onto the nearest pallet with space. Crates you set down while carrying get the same treatment. Anything left over when every pallet is full parks at the cellar elevator instead of scattering. Both behaviours have config toggles.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Crate crafts pause when there's no room[/b] — vegetable, beer, mead, wine, foodstuff and other crating jobs at the elevator-side benches pause until a pallet can take the result. Crates never end up dropped on the floor mid-craft.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]"Linked to elevator" confirmation[/b] — a small pop-up over each cellar pallet you build confirms it's wired into the elevator and the porter. Toggle off in config for a quieter cellar.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Loose crates sit still[/b] — crates that end up on the floor (instead of on a pallet) used to slowly drift into walls or unreachable areas. They now stack on the spot they landed.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Outside the cellar[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3]In the Town barn, pallets add merchant trading capacity. Anywhere else, they work as extra single-slot containers.[/size]
[*][size=3]Pairs naturally with [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/60]I Build Where I Want[/url] for full placement freedom — drop pallets anywhere on the map.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Other mods of mine you might like[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/60]I Build Where I Want[/url] — place buildables anywhere on the map. Drop pallets wherever you want them.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/62]Where's Ma' Storage[/url] — pools every container's contents into one shared inventory. Pallets join the pool.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/57]Queue Everything[/url] — queue any craft and walk away. Pairs well with the cellar crating benches.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/70]Give Me Moar[/url] — multipliers for drops and craft outputs. More crates means more reason for more pallets.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Configuration[/b][/size]

[size=3]If you installed the required [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack[/url] and this mod is configurable, press F1 in-game to open the config interface.[/size]

[size=4][b]Requirements[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79][size=3]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack at Graveyard Keeper Nexus - Mods and community (nexusmods.com)[/size][/url]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Compatibility[/b][/size]

[size=3]Built and tested against the latest Windows Steam build of Graveyard Keeper. Other storefronts and platforms aren't extensively tested — should generally work, but YMMV.[/size]

[size=4][b]Installation[/b][/size]

[size=3]Installation using Vortex is the recommended installation method. If you wish to install manually, extract the contents of the mod archive into:[/size]

[code]...\steamapps\common\Graveyard Keeper\BepInEx[/code]

